task.summary: remove ng-app attribute for production compiled version as manual bootstrapping of angular is used
updated angularJS and requireJS to current versions

angular-translate was missing in the generated main.js in prod build. Removes standardRequireModules config option for now so that only one require() call is in main.js with a hard-coded dependency list.
as angularJS doesn't update resolved promises in templates automatically anymore, we have to set the scope variable manually after resolved promise by $translate
removed useless code, it was not used in any part of the demo application
updated to current versions of angularjs, requirejs and angular-translate
removed bootstrap2 CSS, added bootstrap 3.3.0 and fontawesome less files
added translations folder as preparations where translations should be located
updated html structured and classes for bootstrap 3.3
1. updated html structure and classes for bootstrap 3.3 2. use processhtml instead of targethtml to filter html during production build
